<Link id="l00939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="939"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// SwitchToNewBasicBlock - This method is used to jump to a new basic block.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="940"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This function handles the actual updating of block and instruction iterators</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00941" /><CodeLine lineNumber="941"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// as well as execution of all of the PHI nodes in the destination block.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="942"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="943"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This method does this because all of the PHI nodes must be executed</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="944"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// atomically, reading their inputs before any of the results are updated.  Not</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="945"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// doing this can cause problems if the PHI nodes depend on other PHI nodes for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="946"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// their inputs.  If the input PHI node is updated before it is read, incorrect</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="947"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// results can happen.  Thus we use a two phase approach.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
